# AKOS Area Governance (v2)

Use this rule when chartering or maturing an O5-1 area under
`docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/`, or when running an area / harmonization
/ wave-close sweep. Codifies **D-IH-93-B** (area-governance meta-process; 17th
Quality Fabric specialty) **+ D-IH-94-A** (v2 — 2-D maturity model). Mechanical
companion to
[`AREA_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/AREA_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md) v2.

## v2 model in one screen

- **16 components × L0–L5 maturity** over **8 areas** (Data, Tech, Finance, Marketing,
  Operations, People, Research, **Legal**).
- **Critical** components must reach **L3** (Defined) for an area to be **COMPLETE for tier**;
  enhancing components are weighted, never gating. AREA-09 (paired SOP+runbook) is **enhancing**
  (pairing-cliff forward debt; calibration finding I94 P1).
- Each area declares a **kind** (stream_aligned / platform / capability_meta / delivery_capacity)
  + **entity** (Holistika / Think Big / HLK Tech Lab) per `AREA_KIND_ENTITY`.
- New components: **AREA-14 KIND+ENTITY**, **AREA-15 PLACEMENT-INTEGRITY** (no drift + ships a
  contract), **AREA-16 FILE-PLAN** (sub-folder = role/sub_area).

This rule does **not** replace the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar agents inherit when touching area
folders, area processes, or area charter markdown.

## When this rule applies

A sweep is in scope when **any** of:

- A new O5-1 area folder or area charter is minted (DATA at I93 P1 is the
  first worked example — do not author Data charter in P0-only work).
- A tranche adds `process_list.csv` / `baseline_organisation.csv` rows for
  an area.
- The operator requests `--matrix` before a harmonization commit (P8).

Out of scope: chore-only link fixes with no area-structure change.

## RULE 1 — Run the maturity grid + worklist before area CSV commits (binding)

Before landing an area CSV tranche or charter commit, run:

```powershell
py scripts/validate_area_completeness.py --matrix          # 8-area x 16-component grid + crit@L3 tier
py scripts/validate_area_completeness.py --area <Area> --next   # ranked next-action worklist
```

Work the `--next` worklist top-down (critical-first). Disposition residual `gap`/`partial`
findings via inline-ratify per the canonical §5–§6. **Closure gate = `crit@L3` tier COMPLETE**,
not the % score. Do not treat a green People row as proof all areas are ready.

## RULE 2 — Conservative evidence posture (binding)

- **AREA-10** (Supabase mirrors): emit `skip`/L0 unless mirror evidence is explicitly in
  scope — do not invent PASS from repo-only scans.
- **Marketing**: `process_list.csv` uses area code `MKT`, not `Marketing`.
- Emit `L0` (not a higher level) when live evidence is unavailable (deterministic posture).

## RULE 3 — Kind/entity + pattern + file-plan on area work (binding)

- New area-governance processes MUST set `inherited_pattern_id=pattern_area_buildout` on the
  `process_list.csv` row unless a narrower pattern is operator-ratified in `DECISION_REGISTER.csv`.
- Every area MUST declare its **kind + entity** in `AREA_KIND_ENTITY` (AREA-14).
- Area **sub-folder names MUST FK** to a `baseline_organisation` role/`sub_area` (AREA-16);
  structural folders (`canonicals`, `dimensions`, `programs`, `_templates`, `_assets`) are exempt.
- An area's canonicals MUST belong to it (AREA-15) — area-operational disciplines live in their
  consuming area, not parked in People (the methodology-vs-operations boundary).

